    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>HCN emission in the bar of NGC 2903, mapped with the IRAM-30m, exhibits
an enhancement in the leading edge relative to the trailing edge. The
HCN(1–0) integrated intensity is 5.5 times higher in the bar than in the
center. We propose to map with ALMA the HCN(1–0) emission on both sides
of the bar. The spatial resolution (∼4.2”) will allow us to compare the
distribution of the HCN(1–0) with the optical bar (dust lane) and the Hα
distribution. Its distribution, if confined in the bar or downstreaming,
will constrain the two modelisations describing the gas distribution and
kinematics, N-body/sticky particles or SPH. In the latter, shocks are
developing on the leading edge of the bar and the gas is flowing inward
to the center. Possible formation of HCN(1–0) in these shocks and the
relation with the star formation (SF) will be analyzed: correlation
between SF and HCN(1–0) or CO(1-0) emission, mass surface density of the
dense gas, sharp velocity jumps, star formation efficiency.</prp:abstract>
